descript.abstract: Terrestrial Biomes (layer) is a symbolized and labeled display presentation of the World Wildlife Fund Terrestrial Ecoregions data set. The geographic and attribute data of World Wildlife Fund Terrestrial Ecoregions are symbolized and labeled to create the layer. All features are uniquely symbolized based on the BIOME attribute and labeled by class based on the ECO_NAME attribute.
descript.purpose: Terrestrial Biomes (layer) provides a common and useful display of World Wildlife Fund Terrestrial Ecoregions for a better understanding of the data set contents. Add this layer to a map to display useful information about the data set and that integrates well with other data set layers.
